title: SpaceX plans key NASA demonstration for next Starship launch
summary: SpaceX could attempt a key demonstration for NASA during the third test flight of its towering Starship rocket, according to the federal agency.

title: Aalyria wins ESA contract and establishes European arm
summary: Aalyria won a European Space Agency contract to develop an orchestration system for space-based, airborne, maritime and ground-based nodes.

title: India reveals that it has returned lunar spacecraft to Earth orbit
summary: India now credibly has the third most advanced deep-space program in the world.

title: Daily Telescope: An ancient galaxy behind a veil of dust
Orbit Fab and Australia’s Space Machines Company cooperate on in-orbit servicing
summary: Australian in-space servicing startup Space Machines Company announced plans Dec. 5 to work with U.S. on-orbit refueling startup Orbit Fab to validate key technologies.

title: Data rights limitations affecting NASA technology development
summary: Development of a key capability NASA needs for exploration of the moon and Mars is being hindered by limited access to data from companies working on those capabilities.

title: India returns Chandrayaan-3 propulsion module to Earth orbit
summary: The spacecraft that transported the Chandrayaan-3 lander to the moon has returned to Earth orbit, a demonstration of technologies to support a future Indian lunar sample return mission.

title: SatixFy handed stock exchange delisting warning
summary: SatixFy is the latest space firm to face being kicked off a stock exchange after shares plummeted following a merger with a Special Purpose Acquisition Company (SPAC), a fast-track alternative to traditional initial public offerings of stock.

title: Industry report: Demand for satellites is rising but not skyrocketing
summary: A new report predicts that around 20,000 new satellites will launch by the end of the decade — a more conservative forecast compared to other sky-high projections.

title: York reveals latest commercial space-as-a-service mission
summary: York Space Systems established contact within three hours of the Dec. 1 launch of a commercial space-as-a-service mission for CACI International.
